On march 23, 2009
[None]
Laurelai...

Hi!

I hope it helps...

To get the pearl first you have to combat against the Water Elemental in the university and kill him, you will win a status, with that status you will be able to cross swiming from the port to the Islands.

There you have to go to the "Mutants Falls" (is an island but IÂ´m not soure about the correct translation here) there you have to talk with Hydragol the Master, he will ask you about something, then you have to go back to the port and talk with Padamonje, he will give you the Neufar Leaves (another status). You return to the Mutants Falls and give the Neaufar Leaves to Hydragol finally he will give you the pearl.

With the pearl all your Dinoz recover 5 HP at 00:00 time of the server, if they are in the fountain of youth.

On april 12, 2009
[None]
Why is it so difficult to keep your dinoz alive?

DinoParc, the game this evolved from, makes it even harder. You're in a PvP environment from the first turn, and might get attacked a half dozen times by dinos 3 levels higher than yours while you're away waiting for the next turn. This game protects you from that, and lets you battle weaker foes. Even if you die, you have a free Angel Potion (2 after you've done the early missions).

that defense value is determine by what type of dino you are. if you are fire dino, fire defense is neutral, cloud and thunder defense is weak while earth and water defense are strong. This is where the element cycle used.

On may 3, 2009
w3ko
What do you need to cross the river from jumin river to korgon camp to get to the deep gorge?
To cross the river you need the korgon fins, to get those, you need to complete the first mission of Dian Korgsey (spanish name, don't know if it's the same here) at the Korgon Camp. To get there, go to Deep Gorges (you'll need the lantern).

The survival pack (is that the little bagpack?) adds an additional square to your dinoz's combat gear.

if we have a top number of dinoz...is there a way to get rid of some???
You can have infinite dinoz, but only 18 (or 21 with leader skill) will be active, and the rest will be frozen. If you don't like the freezing method, you can sell them at the Tamer Market.

On may 22, 2009
[None]
Hi everyone

I bought my second Dino. Now when they to fight together what's happens to experience points? It will be shared by them? Or everyone wins the whole experience?

Example: A fight with just one gives 8xp

They will win 8 xp each? Or just half?
On may 22, 2009
[None]
Well, unlike the gold, the XP is a set value, based on the enemies you fight, lessened by the level of the Dinoz in the fight.

So that same enemy would be worth less, but there'd likely be more of them. Overall you get less XP than fighting solo.

The XP is divided between the Dinoz, with the higher level one getting a larger share.

An XP benefit, though, comes up when you reach the level-up point.

With a single Dinoz, any battle XP over what is needed to level up is lost (it doesn't even show up in the battle results).

With multiple Dinoz, however, any overflow goes to the other Dinoz (unless they both level up at the same time).

A side effect of this is that, if you DON'T level up a Dinoz that has a full XP bar, both Dinoz's XP gain will go to the one with an unfilled bar.

On july 10, 2009
AndySQdancer
i start with a first level dino.
When i level up, i catch so i choose "strenght"
I level up again and i catch so i choose to "unlock second level skill".
I level up for the third time, catch and i choose burning claws.
On the fourth level up, with ...

Can i pick smashroom hunters?
Or i only have the "second level skill" available when i unlocked them?

"unlock second level skills" is it necessary just one for ever? Or is better to finish ALL of my first level skill before to unlock the second level one?

No, the unlock only unlocked the skills Martial Arts and Charge. Way you leveled up, you would have to Unlock again. If you are not going to immediately use or need the unlocked skills, it is better to get the lower level skills first before unlocking. This saves you an unlock(s) as you level up.

But say you really wanted Warlord early for some reason. Take Strength, unlock, Martial Arts, unlock, Vigilance, unlock, Warlord. This only requires 7 level ups in . But if you took all the lower level skills first before unlocking it would take at least 25 level ups. Thus you can get Warlord with anywhere from 7 to 25 level ups, or more if you chose other level 4 skill(s) before Warlord.

[None]
I have the skill "Sympathetic" and in the description it says "The Dinoz can be followed by an additional Dinoz" Does that mean that if I buy another Dinoz, he will be able to follow my Dinoz? If not, what does it mean?
On august 5, 2009
[None]
You can group your dinoz if they start their turn in the same location. One or two dinoz can choose the Action Follow, and they will then move and fight along with leader of the group. The default limit in a group is 3. If the leader of the group has Sympathetic, he can have an additional follower, making the group maximum 4. The skill Charisma has the same effect, and stacks with Sympathetic, so if the leader has both, his group size can be up to 5 dinoz (himself, plus 4 others).
On august 5, 2009
w3ko
pteroz has 70 HP, right ? how much is his attack ?
Yes, it has 70 . The Dark Pteroz is very fast and uses Flight to protect himself from ground attacks. He also uses Focus and Wrath to increase his offensive power, so the damage he can inflict in your dinoz depends on your dinoz's level. Your wanwan can take the challenge, go ahead.

POTAATO
uBaH, each location will only invoke exactly 1 type of collection skills. So if you're at Frish Port, only the C skill be available. If you're at The fountain of Youth, only C skill.

If your dino has C skills from different elements, you'll get the chance to collect different ingredients as it moves from place to place.

One thing to note, you can only use your C skill once per turn, but it doesn't count towards your turn, so you'll still be able to move/fight/rest.

When can you actually get equipment for your dino, and how?
On september 28, 2009
Zephides
Equipment is for example food. You can put a Battle Ration or a Cloud Burger into you gear, so they can heal themselfs when fighting. They won't always use it, because it's still all random. If you want to put it into your Combat Gear, press the arrow in your inventory.

There are more things that you can put into your Combat Gear, such as reinforcements and shields.
On september 28, 2009
[None]
... and if you want to un-equip anything, double click it. It returns back to your common inventory.

Useful for equipping recovery food before fighting a big monster such as the elementals or strange Dinoz, but then saving them if they are not used. You can then use them on another Dinoz.

The battle ration recovers UP TO 20 hp. Unfortunately it may trigger in a small battle and only recover 3 hp. These are good to save as above.

Zephides
First you'll need the zor's gloves. To get them dig up 3 items: Swamp Mud (sticky swamp), Pure Water (fountain of youth) and Basalt Shard (basalt slopes).
Then move to the Underwater Dome and talk to the Archsage, you'll need to fight the earth elemental.
After that head to mutant falls and talk to master hydragol, he will give you waterlilly pads.
And now, finally, you can move over to Grumhell Forest
